Ogoune v1.0.0 Release Notes
Date: March 2026

Community Edition is now stable with a zero-external-dependency default setup.

Highlights
- Monitoring: HTTP/HTTPS, TCP, DNS, SSL expiry alerts (J-30/J-14/J-7/J-1), domain expiry alerts (WHOIS), SSL/domain metadata enrichment.
- H2 update: optional ICMP monitoring is now available behind `ENABLE_ICMP=true`, with capability-aware monitor creation, startup-safe graceful degradation, and incident network diagnostics.
- Alerting: confirmation window (N consecutive failures), flap detection, cooldown (single down alert per incident), timed reminders, component-level grouping, startup retry for pending notifications.
- Incidents: automatic lifecycle (create/resolve), rich diagnostics, human-readable causes, event timeline.
- Notifications: SMTP and webhooks (Slack, Google Chat, Teams, Discord, generic HTTP), enabled_by_default channel behavior.
- Status page: public unauthenticated page, component aggregation, 90-day uptime bars, dual entrypoint support, maintenance windows (one-time + cron).
- Infrastructure: SQLite embedded mode, PostgreSQL + Redis/Asynq stack, in-process TimingWheel scheduler, monitor detail auto-refresh, API keys (read/read_write), TOTP 2FA, components/tags/organization.

Licensing
- Community Edition: AGPL v3.
- Enterprise Edition: proprietary (internal/ee).

Notes
- Open Core model maintained.
- Community Edition remains first-class and is not intentionally degraded.
